<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Senior AI Engineer with a hardware background, exploring LLM optimisation on RISC-V"
>
  <div class="page">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Paddy McNabb — an AI Engineer with a Ph.D. in Power System Dynamics and a first-class
      M.Eng in Electronics &amp; Electrical Engineering from the University of Edinburgh.
    </p>

    <p>
      Over 19 years I've built production AI and ML systems across Energy, Financial Services, and the
      Public Sector.
    </p>

    <p>
      This blog is where I document my work on edge-scale evaluation of LLM performance
      on RISC-V, from classic benchmarks down to micro-architectural profiling. The aim is always to
      understand exactly where performance is gained or lost, right down to the instruction level, 
      where the RISC-V ISA is fully open and extensible by design..
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

